Name: n-Nonadecane
Description: Nonadecane is a straight-chain alkane with 19 carbon atoms. It has been found as a component of essential oils isolated from Artemisia armeniaca. It has a role as a plant metabolite and a volatile oil component.

fish_seafood_concentrations.Value: Barnacle samples collected from five locations in the Arabian Gulf had concentrations of nonadecane ranging from trace to 690 ng/g(1). Catfish samples collected from seven locations in the Arabian Gulf had concentrations of nonadecane ranging from <0.1 to 29 ng/g(2).

sediment_soil_concentrations.References: (1) Hori T et al; Bull Environ Contam Toxicol 83: 455-461 (2009)
sediment_soil_concentrations.Value: SEDIMENTS: Nonadecane was detected in sediment samples from 14 sites along from the Shinano River in Japan, from Nov 2005 to April 2006, at concentrations ranging from less than 0.1 to 32 ng/g(2).

sediment_soil_concentrations.References: (1) Rushdi AI et al; Arch Environ Contam Toxicol 49: 457-470 (2005)
sediment_soil_concentrations.Value: SOIL: During winter 2002 soil and sand samples, from six locations in the Riyadh metropolitan area of Saudi Arabia, were examined for extractable organic matter; nonadecane was detected at relative concentrations between 0.03 to 6.06% (of total extractable organic matter) at five of six locations(1).
